The paper presents a visual odometry system for an autonomous vehicle, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The system uses a semantic segmentation model and feature matching, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions bundle adjustment, which is a common optimization technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
